commitResults.messageTitle: added Main.java and Duke.java added greet() method to Duke.java
added echo() method to Duke.java updated Main.java to support Duke.echo()
changed echo() method and added exit() method to Duke.java updated Main.java to support Duke.exit()

---Duke.java--- added private variable "tasks" as a String array to store user-instructed tasks add private variable numberOfTasks to keep track of the number of user-instructed tasks replaced echo() method with add() method to support "add task" functionality added listTasks() method to support listing of all tasks functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
---Main.java---
minor changes to support Duke.listTasks() and Duke.add()

---Duke.java---
[changed] variable "tasks" now stores a reference to a Task array instead of a String array
[added] evaluate() method to handle various user input requests (which was originally handled in Main.java)
[added] markAsDone() method to giving Duke the ability to mark tasks as done

---Main.java---
[removed] no longer evaluates user input instructions for Duke; functionality is ported over to Duke.java

commitResults.messageTitle: The following java files are added to support Duke's ability to handle various task types: [added] ToDo.java [added] Deadline.java [added] Event.java
commitResults.messageBody:
---Main.java---
minor changes to handle null user inputs on launch

---Duke.java---
minor changes to improve user interface
[added] new functionality to identify and handle different task types
[added] exitWithoutInstructions() method to handle null user inputs

commitResults.messageTitle: Shifted java files into new directory
Duke can now handle inappropriate user commands [added] InvalidDukeCommand.java [added] VoidDukeCommand.java [added] WrongDukeCommand.java
Duke now has the ability to delete tasks as instructed by user
